						               													<description>A table-top wargame for 2 or more players. It&amp;rsquo;s all about giant monsters, big cities, monsters in big cities, monsters thrashing big cities&amp;hellip;you get the jist of it. The core rules are less than a dozen pages, and there&amp;rsquo;s also a bare-bones rules-lite version of it. Regular updates with new monster packs, some expansion packs, and so on.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Honoring cinema&amp;rsquo;s greatest giant monsters!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Giant Monster Invasion! is a simple tabletop miniatures wargame intended for use with 5&amp;quot; - 7&amp;quot; models (adaptable to 3&amp;quot; - 4&amp;quot; models).  The play area is constructed using available terrain and buildings.  Figures are given in-game attributes and abilities based, primarily, on appearance and/or notoriety.  A &amp;quot;monster point&amp;quot; mechanism is used to achieve team equality.  Play proceeds in player turns (2 or more teams are allowed), taken sequentially.  Rules primarily deal with monster movement and attacks.  Play continues until a single team remains.  Several advanced, optional rules are included.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
